<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="479" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1607,2030]" pageId="12" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1859,1885]" pageId="12" pageNumber="479">Remarks.</emphasis>
The studied specimen (MNHN-IM-2013-67040) conforms well with the 
<typeStatus box="[1153,1201,1860,1886]" pageId="12" pageNumber="479">type</typeStatus>
material. It has four gills on each side, and a radula 
<quantity box="[494,579,1895,1922]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
long with 34 transverse rows of mature teeth. Each granule of the tegmentum of the studied specimen has five pores of aesthetes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1607,2030]" pageId="12" pageNumber="479">This species differs distinctly from its congeners by having 4 gills, quincuncially arranged granules on the tegmentum and intersegmental areas and marginal chitinous bristles with needle-like spines at their tip.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
